caption: Update your google info. We tried to go here last night and it was closed!!😭

(Translated by Google) Looks like the sea !!  (Original) On dirait la mer !!

(Translated by Google) Food selection is limited. A court was over. Music was good. Eat quite well. Quite expensive.  (Original) Essensauswahl ist nur begrenzt. Ein Gericht war aus. Musik war gut. Essen ganz gut. Recht teuer.
If your looking for nice intimate setting to enjoy some jazz this might work for you. If your looking for a place to eat.. not so much. The food was subpar. Our server should be replaced.
Good music. Interesting food. Ok with children.
Great vegan options, cozy atmosphere and good music.

We were there on a Saturday night while the Shotgun Jazz Band was playing. It took about 30 mins to get a seat for dinner, but the hostess managed that experience impeccably. Our server, Jess, was super attentive and very engaging around what to drink and eat. We ended up with delicious cocktails, delicious food, a great view of the band, and an experience to remember. Don’t miss this gem on Frenchmen!
Amazing food and atmosphere, even better service. It’s not too loud, so if you’re looking for a fun, chill place to enjoy some music on Frenchman street, this is your place!
very nice atmosphere, and classy jazz music.

A cozy restaurant and bar with great cocktails and tasty small plates! We arrived before the rest of our group and the hostess kindly escorted us in since it was cold out. We ordered some cocktails. I got the Rif, which is the bartender's creation of the day. It was a take on a whiskey sour and was boozy and delicious! My fiance ordered the Chai cocktail which tasted pretty similar to mine. I didn't get a lot of chai flavor. They pushed some tables together for our rowdy group of 6. The waitress was extremely patient with us and was willing to chat and laugh with us. She made our experience even better! She suggested two plates per person, I would suggest one small plate and one solo dish per person. Thankfully, no one was super hungry because these plates are small! We ordered the bacon wrapped dates, the braised quail, the Israeli couscous, the fish tacos, shrimp tempura, and pommes frites. The couscous was so amazing!! I'm going to try to make it myself. The dates, pommes frites, and tacos were great. The braised quail was small but the jambalaya was good. And the shrimp tempura was more like popcorn shrimp. Would skip that one next time. The musicicians were a quiet piano soloist and a duo. We were overpowering them with our talking (sorry!) and they didn't really add to the ambiance. The food and drinks were delicious and the place was cozy. Better for a date night or quiet night for a couple rather than a rowdy group like we were.
(Translated by Google) Good music and well made cocktails  (Original) Buona musica e cocktails fatti bene
Great drinks, great atmosphere, great music!
The clementines put on a nice show! Food was tasty too!
The best chicken and sausage gumbo I have ever had was here at Three Muses. Servers were not as great.
Delicious cocktails, bites menu and impressive jazz band- The Royal Roses, made for a great Madi Gras evening. Thank you all for an enjoyable evening!
Had a blast. Get to be close to the band and the food was delicious. Would for sure go again.
Really tasty sharing plates. Friendly staff. Interesting jazz. Much more intimate than other places in NOLA which is refreshing when you're tired from sitting ontop of people all day long.
Nice classic live jazz place. Tourists need passport to order drinks though.
Great music!!!!
Great food, great cocktails and a jazz band playing in the background. One of my favorite places in NOLA.
Good music, bartender/manager with a nasty bad attitude

They serve tapa style food meant for sharing. We shared the quail, bulgogi bowl, fish tacos, gumbo, and meatballs. It was really good. The live music was beautiful. Really enjoyed the vibe of this place.
Relaxed atmosphere, drinks, and music.
Fun dinner location
The place for Swing-Jazz bands.
Food, service, both excellent. Music and atmosphere first rate. Loved this spot.
The cocktails were just perfect. It was a beautiful. You might want to call in and try to get a reservation if you are planning to get dinner though.
A little French jazz and really good tacos made for a fun evening on Frenchmen St. I would definitely go back next time I'm in NOLA!
Delicious food and great jazz!
The staff was extremely pretentious and treated me like I was beneath them. The live music took at least thirty minutes to get stared. I would not recommend
Fantastic food, great service, excellent cocktails and some of the best music in town. This place is always a highlight in a city full of the greatest music and food on earth!
Always delicious!
There was really strong bad smell of bleach detergent. Food was not good either.

The live music lineup here is fantastic. I've been 3x and have always stayed for at least 2 hours. Drinks and food are solid too. Recommendation is to come for dinner so you can sit at a table or expect to have a late night snack as tables are for dining only. Otherwise stand at the bar or grab a limited number of the bar seats. One drink minimum. Be sure to tip your musicians!
One of the many places you must visit when in New Orleans. Good food and drinks with wonderful bands.
Excellent food! Great music but come for the food and drinks!
Small place but excellent food and drinks. Live music was top notch too without a cover or fee. Loved it!
Good food, great staff and spectacular music with an unexpected Pfister sister joining Meschiya Lake during her set.

The band playing was talented. However we went there for drinks and our Canadian driver licenses were not accepted by the bartender, when no other bar had any problems with them. We left after having a soda, so can't comment on drinks or food.
Great spot for a low-key jazz!

Outstanding.  Great quiet atmosphere, perfect setting for the wonderful jazz group we enjoyed, while sharing small plates.  The various dishes were either "Shared" or "Solo" offering in a short menu something that will no doubt satisfy most.  The setting was ideal as a small relaxed club for quality jazz.  The staff, attentive and joyful.  Very nice for couples or small groups.
Great food better service good music
Loved this place. Loved the waiter who was hilarious as hell. Loved the music. Jazz so good you shut up to listen to even though it's ok to talk over it. Fun small apps for the menu.

I really liked this place, was a good small bar with some great live music. it was pretty mellow when we went, which was a nice break from the other spots we had been that day. The drinks were reasonably priced and the bar tender was friendly.
Beautiful place. Really comfortable. Excellent service and the food is amazing.
Great cocktails...Food was fantastic.
Good food, good music, good service. A quiet, classy oasis.
Perfect spot on Frenchmen street!
Great food,  wonderful service and great music. A must visit when you are in New Orleans.
Friendly, helpful, honest staff. Delicious food. Great music.
Tasty small plates and great music.
Jazz and whatever else you're craving.. this is a place that's sure to deliver. Wonderful cocktails and pleasant food a perfect accompaniment to the music
Delicious shareable dishes, amazing live music, & humorous wait staff.
Great and friendly staff. The food is a foodies dream. Great Live music and you can still talk and visit with friends!! Matthew was fantastic
Wonderful live jazz. Really good menu of small plates and great choice of local beer. Staff were ace. Must visit place.
Amazing music, great food
Great music throughout the evening. Fun vibe without being too loud, and excellent cocktails (& wine), food (try the apps), and service (very friendly).
Good food and good music

Been twice. First night food was passable, one of the artists was great then the following act, kind of 1920s country meets Zydeco was dull as dishwater. Went again a few nights later and the food was really bad. Confit duck was tough and dry. Seriously how can you make duck confit dry? Freeze it and reheat it several times maybe? I also chose the roasted Brussel sprouts done in an “Asian style” with crunchy sesame. They came in a sweet and sour sauce with broken uncooked instant ramen noodles on top. I’m guessing the chef was on acid to try to pass that off. Never been a fan of uncooked instant noodles sprinkled over my sprouts. My friend ordered the cous cous which was under mains and sounded tasty.  But she said it just was plain cous cous with hardly anything added to it. Cocktails were nice. Would never eat there again.
Awesome ambience.. Good music and drinks

(Translated by Google) Good setting, pleasant atmosphere, good food, but the portions are very small, in the end it is quickly expensive to eat to its heights  (Original) Bon cadre, ambiance agréable, cuisine bonne, mais les portions sont très petites, au final cela revient vite cher pour manger à sa faim

Great 20s and 30s jazz with the Royal Roses. Small venue with no smoking and a great bar. Lots of craft cocktails, homemade limeade, and small plates with enough variety to make everyone happy. Must trys include lamb sliders, bacon wrapped dates, pommes frites with feta, and israeli couscous. Leave room for dessert too! Peanut butter pie is amazing!!

I don't normally give anyplace 5 stars, but between the  superb drinks, amazing staff , and excellent food I couldn't think of a reason not to. The bartender is as knowledgeable and friendly. The food was amazing, perfect portion sizes. The waiter was amazing!  They earned this rating
truly one of the best dining experiences of my life. next time i fly to NOLA im just gonna get off the plane and go straight here.
Watch tipping they will secretly double it and pocket cash

Great place for solid food, great service, and good music.
It was good to have dinner and listen to live jazz music, but the food options were very limited and sizes small.
Creative drinks, casual atmosphere, music and great food makes this place 5 Stars!
Great place. Food was great. Music is NOLA. Had a wonderful time. Service outstanding
Awesome

We were simply cheering the band once they were done playing. Plus we spent a hefty amount of money there and left a good tip for the people who appreciated our business. However,  I’m not sure I would want to come back as the experience was totally ruined! If you don’t like loud claps and cheers , stay at home

We had a wonderful experience here! The musicians were excellent, it was lovely to see and hear washing board featured in a band! We ordered Bulgogi, Baked cauliflowers with vegetables, and HIGHLIGHT blue cheese stuffed dates wrapped in bacon!!! All the dishes were delightful, with rich and highly unique flavour. Especially, the blue cheese stuffed dates wrapped in bacon blew our mind! Very friendly and welcoming staff. Highly recommended!!!

The History is powerful!
Quite an amazing experience. Great music. Great staff. Great drinks. Great food.

Loved our visit to the place. It's small but intimate. We received great service. What took me a little by surprise is that dinner is kinda tapas, small portions but good regardless. The band that played the night we went was amazing - Shotgun Jazz Band. Definitely will be coming back here next trip to New Orleans.
Outstanding food, Small plates, Good drinks. Loved the atmosphere!

Great place for dinner.  I would definitely recommend bacon dates .  The brussel sprouts were also a must.  We ended up getting two orders of four tacos.  They were light and savory,  so soooooo good.
Love it
Our group tried a multitude of dishes and every one of them was incredible, even the ones I didn't expect to like. By far my favorite restaurant of the trip
Great service.  We had a fun time.

Love their drinks, live music selection (The Clementines were so fun and took me to a 1920s Speakeasy vibe). They also have an excellent selection of small plates. If you feel like noshing on something, try their cheese plate. It showcases excellent, unique cheeses from different parts of the world.
Loved the vibe and live music here! The food portions were very small though.

Good Live Music + Good Food = So Much Satisfaction. Are you really looking for more? I just said they have good food, really good! And they have good music, that's the idea of Frenchman St. right? It ain't gonna get better.  Plates are small so don't expect getting stuffed. But tastes all over you? That's the right place. Superb staff too...
Excellent food
Nice spot on Frenchman. Good music and quick bar service.
Good music
Fantastic tapas and sharing plates. Great original drinks, too.
Excellent live music
Great atmosphere, music, service.....my only slight criticism was a lack of fresh salad/veg options on the menu.....but that's just being picky!!! Great experience, will definitely come back ...
Yummy with lovely live music

small restaurant with live music that feels very quaint and personal.  They ask you to spend 90 minutes at the table and if you want to stay longer to move to the bar.  Tempura shrimp and fish tacos were good.  Brussel sprouts were nice but slightly undercooked and the couscous was underwelming.

We had s wonderful 1 year anniversary dinner here with good music, interesting food and great service. The desserts were divine as well. This is a perfect place to try a bit of everything and share each dish with the one you love. We shared the yummy brussel sprouts, beef bolgogi, duck and our favorite, the meatballs. Definitely an interesting and tasty mix of flavors. For dessert we had the peanut butter brownie pie with whip cream and 2 scoops, one of blueberry sherbert and the other vanilla, with cookies. We finished off out meal with a sweet ruby port. A memorable and delightful evening.
Great food wonderful atmosphere
Thanks Matt Underwood and Monty Banks!

The food was amazing!  We had the evening special of Crawfish and Ramp Gratin and it was by far the best thing we had in NOLA in our four day stay!  Chef Gibbons deserves accolades for the food he has imagined and prepares!  We are true “foodies” and the subtle yet distinct flavors he creates are worth a visit when you are in NOLA!! Recommend highly!

Absolutely made my trip. A local recommended us go to Frenchmen St and after reading up on it I chose to make reservations at Three Muses and boy I'm glad I did...it was the last spot! Don't go without a reservation, especially  on a Friday/Saturday. I dont why there are bad reviews, I guess people don't get out much or have never been to a tapas bar before... The food was outstanding, my service was awesome even being there so late. The music vibe was incredible, and a gentlemen even came in off the street and joined the house musician and it was so whimsical. My most memorable place from this trip. I thought everything was priced accordingly. We had the Pommes Frites, the tempura shrimp, braised meatballs, grilled lamb and a special item I can't remember the name. Amazing. Next time I go to NOLA Im def stopping by.

Nice place and atmosphere, servers were very nice abd friendly. Service was quick and the food was good. However the menu was set up confusingly and the portions we're small, to the point where our waitress recommended getting two meals. Overall a good experience

Wonderfully quaint back street find! Food was great! Jess -our server-was super nice and attentive! Other 2 servers also pinched in and brought out food. Atmosphere was laid back and energetic all at the same time. Piano music was superb! Hostess could have not been so snobby. We were there quite early -only one other table had a customer- and she tried seating us behind a pole. She didn't like it when we asked for a table closer to a window. She then said we had to be done in an hour and a half.  Even with a relaxed meal and  quality listening to music we left with a few minutes to spare. The couple that was seated before us was still there and we never heard her mention the time limit to anyone else. Overall I would recommend a visit!

awesome jazz!! and yummy gumbo. friendly service.

Not bad, but not great. Went in expecting Jazz and got Country music.

The thing that ticked me off most was that we weren’t allowed re-entry after stepping out for a moment. This was after spending over $100 for 2 and moments before the new band began playing. A nice quiet space to enjoy some live music without losing the ability to have a conversation.  Small plates - try the lobster Rangoon and the meatballs!
my favorite place in nola

Very unpleasant the hostess was very rude and there was other unkindly people working there it was a very uncomfortable experience I will definitely not be going back there ever but I can say the food was delicious.
Actually, I was disapointed according to good rates seen: the food is very simple, even the music was not exciting. I did not spent a bad evening, but was expecting better

I don’t normally write reviews, but I really felt the need tonight.... with that being said the food was great our server Jennie was wonder, but all other staff was so rude.  Our company had a first meet at greet schedule at this restaurant, but we will never be back.  I can deal with a few rude behavior, but not a whole meal.  Save your money and go somewhere with respectful staff!!!
Fantastic live music in an intimate bar setting.
Wonderful place ! We enjoyed the live music while eating and the great dinner. Nice menu,  something different but absolutely amazing ! Great service.
Small quaint place with live music. The tapas were good.
Spent a wonderful evening of music and great food. Highly recommend.
Amazing food, great jazz
Great food and music venue. The lamb sliders and rice bowl kill it every time.
Good food and quality interesting music. We loved it here. Quite touristy early evening, but definitely worth a visit.
Proactive and knowledgeable wait staff.
I spent a beautiful evening at the Three Muses'. Music was great, food was very good although the portions were small. Service was good. A perfect place to spend our last night in New Orleans.

Tappas like menu.  Fish tacos gluten free and very delicious.  They do have gluten free choices. Our table also shared a carpacio dish, meatballs, lobster Rangoon  lamb sliders, and pomme frit.  We enjoyed them all.  Also some fun cocktail choices. One of the nice features is live music.  Definitely recommend having reservations.
Bartender on point, great cocktails that are creative and well balanced. We love the small plates and Wednesday night for the Hot Club!
Food selections were fantastic!!  Great service, good jaz, nice environment.   Would go back again.
Great tapas, cocktails and music. Food is a little pricey, but worth it for the entertainment.
The tempura shrimp were amazing

Small and medium plates, one more delicious than the next, a cozy, interesting decor and atmosphere, a great server ( thanks Jess), live music and a great location make this a not to be missed restaurant. Order several plates and share everything. Do not skip dessert. The caramel drizzled apple crisp and house made ice cream and cookies are essential!

A tofu rice bowl with kimchi, cauliflower and carrot crostini and the pommes frites have a vegan option as well.  Show up early, much like all places on Frenchman, they fill up fast!

The best cocktails we had in all of New Orleans! The mac and cheese was unfortunately pretty overcooked, but would come back just for the drinks!
Small plates were delicious. Go sit, listen to music, and feel fancy.
Nice music and food. Surprisingly low attendance .

OK, so I think I like the idea of this place more than the actual place. The atmosphere and the food, and the music are all great.  The stage is small so the musical acts are usually smaller, and not too amplified. You can get up close to the musicians and really get into the music.  The reason why I gave it 3 stars is the price of the food. I just can't get past the price. Way too expensive! I think I'd rate it 4 or 5 otherwise.
Good drinks

Nice and cozy place with a varied menu at great prices and lovely service

Great small plates to share! Front door guy in a hat glasses and blue shirt with a Miller High patch was  VERY RUDE! Waiter was attentive. great music...great experience other than rude dude at the front door
Awesome place and great staff😀

Had a lovely dinner with shared small plates, whisky and cocktails, and live music. Friendly service and quality gourmet food. Enjoyed Crispy Pork Belly, Lamb Sliders with baby pickles and ginger, and chocolate mousse pie.
Interesting tapas  good service very good unusual music and acts hipster atmosphere on an awesome Street
Nice service, good food

neat place with great food and great entertainment. highly recommended, perfect venue to see live music and eat with teenage children. Very small so  make a reservation before you walk around and see the area.

I would come here again for sure! I had a lovely kale salad, mouth watering mac & cheese, and a yummy drink that featured some sort of pepper, maybe jalapeno? I don't remember I drank a lot this trip. Anyhow, they also have a nice live band. The bar tender was a super sweet lady who made the experience even better. Super bonus, the neighborhood it's in is dope. There was this local band playing outside that had the whole street dancing. Great time.
Great food, great service, and great music!

Interesting place, had to go because they didn’t accept international drivers license as ID for drinks !  I wonder if that would be the case if I stayed and I payed by credit card as usual, which also requires ID.
The food is "small plate" style. Everything we tried was delicious and the service was impeccable!
Small space, but that small space enhances the live music. Limited but very delicious menu. One of the best stops on Frenchman.

Tried to get into this place late on a Sunday with 5-10 open tables on not very busy but apparently the female outside smoking and reading her book couldn't be bothered to seat me. She asked me if I wanted lessons in being a host and I went elsewhere. Fun times NOLA, fun times. This was actually the only bad experience I had in my time at New Orleans. Everyone else was so welcoming and great, but not here.

What a gem of a place on Frenchmen's street!! Loved every second of our experience here. Not only was the live band experience awesome - the food was spectacular! Recommend to anyone who likes music and fun.

This place basically has the best food/atmosphere/crew in the entire city of new orleans so if you want food thats going to ruin your perception of literally ANY other food for the rest of your life and cause you to be unsatisfied with all other dining establishments, eat here.
I absolutely loved having dinner here. The small plates were excellent quality, and the entertainment was second to none in providing the jazzy New Orleans atmosphere. Pricey, but worth it.

While in New Orleans on business, I was enjoying all the fantastic live music on Frenchman street. I spent hours going in and out of nearly every establishment.  My experience at the Three Muses deserves mention.  I travel for work and I am in sales.  I speak with strangers easily and make friends everywhere I go.  Which I why this story is so amazing to me. Upon entering this place I noted the amount of people in the Three Muses was very low, maybe 15 people total on a very busy night.  Being alone, I walked up to the bar and ordered a drink.  When I receiving the drink, I took a sip and remarked to the bartender that the drink was great, she said “why wouldn’t it be?”  Hmm, I thought.  Odd response. I turned to the music, as the band was very good.  When the person next to me ordered a drink, I noted some ingredients that I like and asked this same bartender what the drink was called, she glared at me saying nothing.  I thought she could not hear me, so I asked again.  She reached down, grabbed a drink menu and tossed it at me.  I was shocked.  I was trying to imagine what I could have done to make this woman so unkind towards me.  I looked at the younger bartender, that Miss Happy was clearly training and she rolled her eyes at me.  As if to say, “I don’t know why this Manager/Bartender is being so mean to you but I am sorry”  We all know the look.  The young bartender even went so far as to let me try some of the new drinks she was learning, when Miss Happy walked away.  When the Mean employee returned however, she quickly moved away from me and stopped speaking.  The straw that broke the camel’s back was this-  As I was quickly drinking my one and only drink, I asked very nicely “Sweet heart, could you please give me a glass of water, when it is Convenient”  To which she said “Did you just call me Sweetie?”  I responded, I was simply trying to be nice, I am from Texas.  I was being sincere.  The water never came.  I paid my bill and began to leave.  When I asked about the water she stated with a stern look in her eyes.  “You said ‘when it was convenient“ and then sneered at me. Upon leaving, I could not find one single employee who would tell me Miss Happy’s name.  I have never been in a restaurant or bar in my life where every employee was in fear of revealing a person’s name.  They all said things like “Why not ask her?”  “Why do you need to know?”  Clearly, this happens all the time and they cover for her.  Therefore, I will kindly describe the bartender who is scaring all your customers away.  She is a heavyset blonde-haired woman, with pale skin and tattoos up and down both arms.  If you own the Three Muses and you are wondering why your sales numbers do not compare to the other bars on Frenchman, she is working at your bar.  I will never come back here and will recommend people avoid this place.  Your entire staff knows this is occurring, regularly, and they are enabling this person.  It is clear she needs therapy and should not be customer facing.  As a Christian, I will pray for her, she needs it.
Great vibe
Excellent food and great service
Amazing food! Gumbo was to die for, and topped off with an amazing pedal steel player named Dave. Wonderful. Jess was a fantastic server.
Great place. Great cocktails. Great live music. Don't miss Shotgun Jazz Band when they play.
Excelente food and drinks
Great date night! Shared small plates and listened to great music. Get reservations and enjoy the cozy atmosphere.
Fab food, bartender, music....the trifecta!

The look and feel of this place said "awesome.". The food was very below average compared to other New Orleans options.  The waitstaff, music, and bar were all great though.  I was frankly suprise by the poor quality food.  Soggy fries, under seasoned meat, etc.

Very nice bar. The food portions are small, more like  snacks for drinks, not dinner. The drink variety is good, especially for whiskey and bourbon. Prices are reasonable. Bands that play here are very good too and do so for hours. It usually needs a reservation but if you arrive early they can squeeze you in for a table or directly at the bar. There is room for three people in an independent segment at the bar, less in the way to the bathroom, try to nail it!
Great food and better music. Recommended!
Intimate dining with quiet atmosphere. Wonderful food and service.

Always spend an evening at 3 Muses when in New Orleans.  The live music is on point and the food spectacular  -- pork bellies, blue cheese stuffed dates, elevated mac n cheese, gumbo and the lamb chops --  amazing!!
Fun spot
Delicious food and live music. The service was great!
Great experience! Live music on Sunday was just AMAZING! Food is tapas style, full of taste and very well prepared. Awesome place and service!
Very good place to enjoy jazz, the food size is small but good taste. Even reserved a table I waited 1/2hour.
Excellent music, food and kindness!
Great local music, food and drinks

The food was good but not outstanding and the live music was lounge jazz and  ok but not standout (bands vary though, when I went it was just a lone pianist who also sang but it may be different for you). The location is excellent if you are already on Frenchman street and looking for something to eat but I wouldn't recommend going out of your way. All in all 3/5.

I love this place! Our waitress was fun outgoing and energetic! The made great recommendations and made my birthday that much better. This place also has live music, which was beautiful. The food comea out as it ia ready because they do not use heat lamps. Food is freeesssh.

Our first time in New Orleans and the Hostess at the door were very rude. We waited and waited for someone to assist as the sign says wait to be seated; no one arrived we entered and the Hostess asked us in a very rude manner can we help you with something? I kindly asked if a table is available and she said you can wait outside and we'll be with you in a very hostile tone and turned around and walked away. This is not someone that should be in the hospitality industry. There's a way in asking someone to wait. We own our own restaurant in NYC and this is not acceptable. We will not recommend it to anyone. It's the Human Factor that makes the difference...

This is a great local place to hear dome incredible  music, grab a bite to eat and get a fancy cocktail! The staff is friendly extremely professional and efficient. It often times can be very lively, if you starving make reservations!
Cozy place with yummie food and live music
My wife loved the food and atmosphere.
This place is amazing. It has great tapas style food, cocktails, and music.
Great music.  Friendly singer and staff.  Unique tapas style dishes.  Fun cocktails.  Unfortunately no CA red wine, but I coped easily.
Excellent music and nice beer. Frenchmen st. is more quiet and less boozy than Bourbon.
Washboard Rodeo were tight and entertaining. Great music, great musicians.
Awesome bar with live music.
Good bar staff and music. Nice place to hang out and enjoy without being crowded. Easy to get a drink, and they were all well made.
Very, very good

Mm mm good  ... if your able to get  a reservation at Three Muses...go. The atmosphere is intimate,  small tables very small space,  music fills the entire room but isn't so overwhelming that you can't carry on a conversation. The food is served on small plates...perfect for sampling many different flavors. They have a delicious drink menu.. One of the best restaurants in NOLA.
Great music. Great food (but small portions)

It was always the "go to" place until yesterday. My friend and try to get in when the lady at the door checked my ID and goes "sorry, your ID is not federal government issued" and then checked-in my friend with an ID from the same state. She did appologies blaming it on a long day, but I can't ignore the implicit bias.
Quiet, intimate, and incredibly good vibe. Call ahead and get reservations then stuff yo fat face with pork belly!!

Fantastic food and dining experience

(Translated by Google) Good place to dine and listen to live music in New Orleans in the Frenchman area  (Original) Buen lugar para cenar y escuchar música en vivo en Nueva Orléans en la zona de Frenchman
Saw the Royal Roses playing jazz and ate good food. Really enjoyed the atmosphere and chill wait staff. Great, cozy bar with live music.

Small friendly bar. I went early evening. Menu on website was not comparable to the actual menu with a few exceptions. The pork belly on pancake I did have  though was delicious just wish it was a  bit more. Their singer and small band were okay. This place seemed a bit more low key than the other places on Frenchman Street. It was packed though on a Saturday night but I was able to find a place at the small bar area.

Very unique and delicious dishes. The menu changes from time to time. The lamb sliders were delicious. The cocktails are very tasteful. Reservations are highly recommended if you are going when the live music is playing.
Wonderful!
Great vibes, intimate venue to see some great jazz. Nice small plates menu and the IPA Jucifer they have on tap is probably one of my favourites of all time
Nice venue to hear local talent, on Frenchman St. The new Bourbon Street for locals.
Good food, nice music
Crazy hipster nonsense but awesome drinks and good looking food.
Great music and friendly servers and hostess

Three Muses is my "always go to" music restaurant while in Nola. This is a small and delicious plates restaurant. Everything is delicious. I have taken guests here the last two trip and they have raved about the food and entertainment. Dinner at Three Muses and after up the block to the Spotted Cat for more great entertainment. .
Good was good but small portions. Jazz area is very small

smaller restaurant serving a mixture of cultural foods. I order the Gumbo, not disappointed. My date ordered the Bulgogi, also tasty. we were able to squeeze in a table before the reservations started filling the place. it was fairly empty while we were there, but quickly got packed full. The musical act was a folk band trio of sorts with a singer/guitarist, violinist, and the beard holding down the lapsteel. good time, would recommend. make a reservation if you are going on a early spring friday night
Had to wait forever but it was well worth it. A family style restaurant. Interesting food, nice staff and great location. Smack dab in the middle of all the music and action!

Terrible.It seems that "joint" is quite taken with itself. Poor service. We had reservations for 8:30. Got there and the rude wench outside had us wait 10 minutes finally she said we could wait at the bar. Went to the bar, spent 15 minutes being ignored. Finally the wench comes over and takes us to our table which had been vacant the whole time we were there. Sat there for 25 minutes and listened to a mediocre band. Still NO SERVICE, Got up and left, told the wench outside that we were leaving and told her why, she just waved her hand and said OK, whatever or something like that. We went to Snug Harbor and were treated very well. Had the best Gumbo I've had in awhile.  3 Muses=Don't GO, waste of your time. Question for the owner: Is this really the type of restaurant/bar/music you want to present, if not, FIX IT. The customer service is terrible. I got better service at an over-crowded bar on Bourbon St at 10:00pm on a Saturday night. 3 Muses is a joke.
Hole in the wall bar with good drinks and music

Terrible service, incredibly rude server, 30+ minute wait for a drink in NOLA, that is unheard of in that town!!! Server took two of the four orders at our table and never came back for the remaining folks. Who does that ??? Music was fantastic and was the highlight of the dinner. Our server ruined the vibe !!

This was the only place (that I could find) on Frenchmen St that had easy to book reservations. I was planning a small bachelorette party and it worked out really perfectly.  Like others have said, the music was fantastic, and at a level that allowed you to still talk with your table. The servers were extremely sweet and accommodating, and the food was great. We came here after dinner so we kept it small with only the fries and peanut butter pie, but both were great.  I tried an Earl Gray Tea drink that I didn't love but probably because it was strong, so at least you know they are generous.  We had a great time!
Awesome food and amazing music. I will come again during my next visit to NOLA

Very small joint and has live music. Jazzz. Well maintained place. The staff are super friendly. Lots of tables for the space they have !!! Food was very good. Have had one of the best Shrimps here! Definitely recommend to try that.
You simply must have a reservation, darling!

Not impressed. Portions are small, and apparently the 'concept' is to not bring out the meals at the same time.. Each meal came out separately and when the waiter was asked he said "well, the idea is that everyone shares. Perhaps this is not the place for you''. Meanwhile the menu says 'no split checks' (so, really, how does that make sense?). We didn't create a fuss, but will never come back. Do not waste your time- there are plenty of other fantastic restaurants in town.  Edit: reduced to 1 star- bathroom stalls in women's room neither lock nor close completely.
Lovely experience, service superb, music delightful, interesting cocktails & food was good.
Great food, drinks, and music.
This place has excellent and original food options. The beer selection is also good.

I sat at a table and was ready to order when the waitress told me that I had to give up my table to some other customer. There were no lines or any other customer waiting for tables at this time.   I moved to another area and this waitress …
Cozy atmosphere. Great music. Delightful staff. Absolutely Delicious Food! The fish tacos were amazing. Also loved the lamb sliders and gumbo! For desert, try the strawberry shortcake. Yum!
Amazingly intimate atmosphere with good food and superb music

(Translated by Google) Jazzy musical atmosphere, pleasant service. We eat well but the portions are small for a significant price!  (Original) Ambiance musicale jazzy, service agréable. On y mange bien mais les portions sont petites pour un prix non négligeable !
The funnest place to have dinner. Great music, food and cocktails. What else would I need? Not much. It was fantastic.

Chill vibe, excellent entertainment and friendly staff. The bartender was fast and attentive and made a mean whiskey sour. We were so glad our tour guide had recommended the place! It's a far cry from the madness a few blocks away! It's cool and relaxed, definitely a place I would visit again in a heartbeat. We did not have the food, but it looked and smelled amazing!
Great music

one of my favorite eats on frenchman

Very fun place with great food! We had a really good time. I love that the music changes and it's not just one act all night. Very cool.

I don't review restaurants. I have to say that I was moved to make this review.  Absolutely amazing. Everything here was completely on point. The table I was at ordered the stuffed dates, fish tacos, mac and cheese, and steal frites. Everything was outstanding. Tender, delicious steak cooked to perfection. Mac and cheese that blew our collective minds, and the fish tacos that were flavorful and flaky. We had the peanut butter pie, which was also amazing.  Drinks were also terrific. Outstanding local beers I've never tried before, combined with what I can only describe as the best cocktail menu of any small bar I've been to. The muse and earl grey gardens we're absolutely delicious.  Price is a bit steep for portion size. Treat yourself, it's worth it.
Love it. Will always visit when I come to New Orleans.
Great LOCAL taste of New Orleans
Lamb sliders are boss. The feta fries are sublime. The sazerac was on point. Dreaming about the next time we return. Abaline Fallatta was our performer and she was pretty damn incredible.
Did not go in, but it looked OK.

Excellent food and beverages. Local talent was not quite what we were hoping for, more a rockabilly blues style rather than a jazz blues, but still fun atmosphere. Gumbo daily special was solo good we ordered a 2nd helping, and Pork Belly was scrumptious. You have to leave room for the Peanut Butter Pie desert too!

SO Disappointed. Staff were all friendly when we arrived but we were quickly forgotten about. We finished our drinks prior to our meal and so we tried to get the waitresses attention to get another drink for 45 minutes, the runners dropped our plates too quickly for us to mention it to them and when she eventually showed up to clear our table of stacked and empty plates we just asked for the cheque.  I ordered the $15 cheese platter which was an absolute wrought. 3 slices of cheese, 4 small slices of French stick, 4 thin slices of apple, 1 tiny square of pâté and some nuts. Left me hungrier than I sat down but even if I wanted to order something else there was no way of ordering with no waiter. My partners tempura shrimp was again very small but delicious, he was very happy if a little hungry.  To top it off the Musicians were very lack lustre and bored during the show and pushy regarding tips - “$20 is just if you think we’re okay”, I would have tipped better if they hadn’t been so obnoxious about it. They only played for about 20 minutes for the hour or so we were there and spent a good 5 whinging about how they deserved to be out to dinner on a Saturday night too. I’m an artist, I know it’s rough but you make it work and be grateful for what you’ve got.  Such a shame, we were looking forward to a special night out but this was the opposite.
Fantastic small restaurant with great bartenders and live music. Didn't try much food, but what I had (fish tacos) were pretty good.
Amazing food

Food, service and band (Shotgun) were great, but the wait to be seated was long (45 minutes) even with reservations. To be fair, it was a Saturday night, so patrons were lingering longer. It's a fine line to walk - you don't want to seem to …

Great place for food and music!

The pork rillettes... omg... so good.  Cozy little space with great service and good music.
Best area in NOLA and their mac & cheese is probably the best I've ever had.

Gorgeous and great food & drink. The lamb sliders are excellent, the Earl Grey Gardens is simply the best adult beverage I've ever had. The ambiance and atmosphere is incredible. I was worried it'd be too young and full of hipsters for my liking but was proven wrong. Very nice place. Will go back again!
I got pot pie that was good
Great music, and unique ambience . Must have the Sazerac.
Amazing atmosphere. Can both be romantic, as well for meeting with friends. But note you can't stay longer than 1h30, so you better know what time the show starts.
Unreal cocktails, great steak frites. I will be back. You should be, too.

Okay, so ... 1. (kind of a minus) we were given a time limit on our seats. We didn't have reservations, they had seats, but were told we needed to leave in 90 minutes.  The rest are pluses -  2. They had live entertainment. 3. They have a variety of vegetarian options. Mac and Cheese - OMG 4. You have to try the Lamb Sliders - they literally melt in your mouth 5. Dessert, I mean you can't go wrong. 6. Great drink menu - I had their seasonal special, made with apple whiskey, YUM!
Fantastic everything...food, service, crowd, music. Perfect

Food was delicious and flavorful. The band was mellow and added to the nice atmosphere and vibe of the restaurant. Without a reservation it was about a 40 min wait, and since they don't have a cover, the staff goes around with a bucket collecting tips for the band. Overall good experience but the waiter could have been a little more attentive.

An excellent, intimate place to enjoy a lovely meal and live music. This place can get crowded and is very small, but it is worth it for the premuim craft cocktails, small but very well executed menu, and music. They even had a great vegetarian option for my aunt!
Enjoyed the Shotgun Jazz band here today! Get a table or wait for a seat at the bar. Totally worth it. Great drinks and food menu, awesome waitstaff, and the music is delicious (yes)!!!

This was a short love affair. First time we were here, 2 years back, loved it. Thinking now that it was because of  the band that was playing there. This time around though, was put off by the pretentious cartoon of a guy who seated us, making us wait till our reserved time of 10.15, even though there were many tables free at 10. He even let a group of "white" folks without reservation go in as well. The food menu also didn't seem too extensive and couple of my friends who were vegetarians didn't really enjoy their food as well. Not going to go back because of that one "dude"
Fantastical

Food was delicious. Steak fries are to die for. Hubby liked the bulkogi. Loved the muse namesake drink. Staff super friendly, nice little bar atmosphere. Music was just a little to mellow for our taste, but talented musicians.
Great music cozy atmosphere. Service not as attentive. Food is great. No reservation then be ready to wait.
Fantastic  music ( especially after 8pm). Unfortunatelly service is quite strange.
Best lamb sliders i’ve ever had!!!!

Food was great here, we had the parm fries on a happy hour special for $5.  This place is a bit more upscale than the others in the area but nice nonetheless.  The love music however was meh the night we went.  Would I go again? Probably not but still a cool place to check out at least once.
Best food in New Orleans. The fish tacos are To. Die. For! And the service is incredible for somewhere that gets so busy.  Best food I've ever had.

Great music, food, and drinks. One of my favorite spots in New Orleans.

Excellent food and cocktails, friendly servers, good music. Great place on Frenchmen.
Great food, eclectic menu, good cocktails, sweet music

Didn't let us in early in the night, saying it was full even though we could see seats open at the bar and tables. Later they shut door in our face saying they were closing though there was still half an hour at least
Tasty small plates.

Great tapas.  The food is so flavorful.  Add in music to the mix and this place has an amazing atmosphere.  If you come early, it shouldn't be too hard to get a seat but I suggest calling ahead to make a reservation to be safe.
A+ service, hard to get into sometimes, so far, so worth it! These sliders.... Marshall* COME BACK HERE!
It was a very quaint little place in the French Quarter's but we did appreciate the live music and the food was pretty good.

FANTASTIC food. Lamb sliders, bruchetta and the fish tacos were delicious! BUT....let me explain.  The food comes out when it's ready. If you want to graze all night, this is the place. It's not a sit down family dinner. But it's well worth it. Great beer selection! Oh yea---the MUSIC! Go people...just GO!

Excellent dishes and a fine variety of beers and drinks. Usually two performers with great taste. Excellent place for a date!

Fabulous atmosphere, the door staff don't allow it to become overcrowded like a lot of the places. You can enjoy nice food and a drink from a well stocked bar listening to the house jazz band in pleasant surroundings whilst the party rages on outside in the streets.
Hope to visit Three Muses again soon. Great vibe
